{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionPolyp segmentation aims to automatically identify and segment polyp regions within the colon.",
    "Its primary objective is to assist clinical doctors in efficiently and accurately locating and delineating these regions, providing vital support for early diagnosis and treatment of colorectal cancer (CRC) [1].",
    "Polyps exhibit varying sizes and shapes at different stages of development [2,3], and their precise segmentation poses challenges due to their strong adherence to adjacent organs or mucosa [4].In the early stage, polyp segmentation primarily relied on manually extracted features [5,6].",
    "For example, Tajbakhsh et al. [5] proposed a method that utilized shape features and surrounding environmental information to automatically detect polyps in colonoscopy videos.",
    "Iwahori et al. [6] utilized edge and color information to generate a likelihood map and extracted the directional gradient histogram features."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Its primary objective is to assist clinical doctors in efficiently and accurately locating and delineating these regions, providing vital support for early diagnosis and treatment of colorectal cancer (CRC) [1].",
    "Polyps exhibit varying sizes and shapes at different stages of development [2,3], and their precise segmentation poses challenges due to their strong adherence to adjacent organs or mucosa [4].In the early stage, polyp segmentation primarily relied on manually extracted features [5,6].",
    "For example, Tajbakhsh et al. [5] proposed a method that utilized shape features and surrounding environmental information to automatically detect polyps in colonoscopy videos.",
    "Iwahori et al. [6] utilized edge and color information to generate a likelihood map and extracted the directional gradient histogram features."
  ]
